<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">marcvee</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hello,<P><BR>Looked back at the old posts and decided to go o feeroot to solo the spec at lvl 45.  Pulled the one in there, then 2 more came in from outside and joined the fun.  Barely made it out alive.  I tried this again later after scouting arount to make sure I olny saw one, and sure enough the same thing happened.  <P>Can anyone give me an idea for another relatively safe spot in the old world to solo through 45 hell?<P>Thanks,<P>Marcve</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bezil</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">It isn't an old world spot, but I got great xp through 45 and they were still good for quick solo breaks up until 49.  The plagueborne thiefs in DL.  Easy single pulls, and fairly safe.   Just get a port, go to the wizzie spires, cast Sense Undead and run over that way.  Single pull every time with Turning, and the blasted with the current undead DD.  <P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Stewbing</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Marcvee,  If you get too lcose to the cave or the wall while pulling the spec, it will agro the specs in the cave.  It was happening to me for a while too until I tried pulling him the opposite way from the cave.  Since you only have to nuke him 3 times, you still shoulod not get too close to the ogre guards.<P>Hope this helps.<P>------------------<BR>Stewbing<BR>48 Dwarf Cleric<BR>Office of FpH<BR>The Rathe Server<BR>"A real friend is not the one that bails you out of jail. A real friend is the one sitting next to you saying 'That was fun.'"<p>[This message has been edited by Stewbing (edited 02-06-2002).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Javara</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If that spec is taken, next zone over in Rathe Mts there are two troll gaurds that you can single pull and solo also. They are near the middle of the zone, south-west of the totem pole. Looking at the guards the one to the right is a shaman, the one to the left is a sk. The shaman is easier.  Not quite as good exp as the spec though.<P>Between the spec in feerot, grouping for hgs in Rathe, and those two troll guards I spent alot of 45 around there.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
